Argentine Stocks: APSA and Tenaris Advance; Bank Shares Decline

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-03-31T20:38:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/argentine-stocks-apsa-and-tenaris-advance-bank-shares-decline.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4:01 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index rose 0.3 percent to 3,388.03.  Alto Palermo SA (APSA)   rose 3.5 percent to 15 pesos, the
steepest gain in more than two months. The shopping mall
operator will pay an anticipated dividend of 131 million pesos,
according to a statement posted today on the website of the
Buenos Aires stock exchange.  BBVA Banco Frances SA (FRAN)  , the unit of  Spain ’s Banco
Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA, retreated 1.3 percent to 15.60
pesos. Argentine sovereign bond prices fell today, which signals
lower value for banks’ fixed-income holdings.  Grupo Financiero Galicia SA (GGAL)  , the country’s
largest consumer lender, fell 1.1 percent to 5.30 pesos.  Banco
Macro SA (BMA)   lost 0.6 percent to 17 pesos.  Tenaris SA (TEN)   gained 1.6 percent to 104.20 pesos. The
world’s largest producer of seamless steel tubes used in the oil
industry, rose at crude prices advanced.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
